  "abstract": "In agricultural experiments, especially in plant breeding quite often interest lies in estimating different components of genetic variance either for the purpose of studying their relative magnitudes of for estimating certain functions of them e.g. heritability (see Kempthorne and Tandon 1953), average degree of dominance (see Comstock and Robinson 1948) etc...",
